= Formulating the American Rescue Plan

As the senate prepares to pass the American Rescue Plan, we must ensure the bill is to our likings. We plan for stimulus checks, aid to local governments, and a expansion of the child tax credit.

We must figure out how much we want to spend on these provisions. Clawing substancial spending from the corporate {!<span style="color:#6495ED">Demo</span><span style="color:#1F77B4">crats</span>!} will be no easy task.

@arp_main

- @adjust_spending: We can decide the stimulus amount
- @increase_child_tax_credit: We can decide the child tax credit provisions
- @adjust_local_aid: We can decide the funding for local governments
- @end_arp: The bill is ready to go

