We will now move on from editing existing provisions to adding new ones.

@arp_minwage

-@add_min_wage: Now, we will demand a 15 dollar minimum wage as well as student debt relief be added to the bill!

@add_min_wage
subtitle: We promised our supporters we'd do this in the 2020 campaign. We must fufill our promise. 
go-to: arp_fillibuster

We push hard for these key provisions, yet corporate {!<span style="color:#6495ED">Demo</span><span style="color:#1F77B4">crats</span>!} like Manchin and Sinema are refusing to support it! We attempt to change their mind, yet they won't budge, lecturing us on the "harm" it would cause to the economy.

@arp_f_manchin

-@arp_rally_in_states: We will hold rallies in West Virginia and Arizona in support of a 15 dollar minimum wage to pressure Manchin and Sinema to listen to their constituents. 
-@arp_end_everything: We will revisit these issues in 2023, then.

@arp_rally_in_states
subtitle: This will increase the support of {!<span style="color:#6495ED">Bernie</span>} aligned Democrats in primary elections. This will greatly increase inner party dissent.
on-arrival: coalition_dissent += 2; progressive_support_primary += 2; approval_rating += 5

Our rallies bring large crowds of ordinary people inspired to pressure their senators to follow the will of the people. Sinema and Machin are furious, as Schumer is forced to spend valuable time to calm them down. Eventually, the American Rescue Plan passes the senate, and it's signed into law.

@arp_end_everything
subtitle: Our base will be very disappointed
on-arrival: youth_dissent += 8; labor_dissent += 8; approval_rating += 5

Many progressives feel betrayed, angry that you couldn't get minimum wage and student debt relief inside of the bill. Eventually, the American Rescue Plan passes the senate, it's signed into law.